00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:32,184
Who wants to do business with…

706
00:38:32,893 --> 00:38:37,815
the family whose daughter
solicits rape fantasies

707
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:40,609
to attack… a pregnant woman?

708
00:38:40,693 --> 00:38:41,527
[music fades]

709
00:38:43,195 --> 00:38:45,197
[portentous music playing]

710
00:38:47,908 --> 00:38:51,579
[Leslie] Ian and Angela had been together
for eight months at this point.

711
00:38:52,079 --> 00:38:54,832
Michelle was finally out of their lives,

712
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:57,918
and there are twins on the way.

713
00:38:58,711 --> 00:39:04,383
Ian was excited and looking forward
to this new chapter in his life.

714
00:39:04,467 --> 00:39:06,469
[music fades]

715
00:39:07,511 --> 00:39:11,599
But then I am sleeping late at night…

716
00:39:11,682 --> 00:39:13,809
[cell phone vibrating]

717
00:39:13,893 --> 00:39:17,229
I get a call somewhere around 2:00 a.m.,

718
00:39:17,313 --> 00:39:19,815
which is never a good feeling.

719
00:39:20,858 --> 00:39:22,735
The first words out of Ian's mouth are…

720
00:39:24,445 --> 00:39:26,322
"The twins are not real."

721
00:39:26,405 --> 00:39:28,407
[music turns ominous]

722
00:39:30,242 --> 00:39:32,411
I had to kind of re-- like…

723
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:37,249
get my thoughts together,
and I just said, "What? Wait, what?"

724
00:39:37,333 --> 00:39:38,834
And he said,

725
00:39:38,918 --> 00:39:41,003
"The sonogram of the twins…

726
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:43,589
was fake."

727
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:48,052
I'm thinking, "What the fuck?"

728
00:39:48,135 --> 00:39:50,638
You know, Ian confronted Angela.

729
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:53,724
And Angela was

730
00:39:54,392 --> 00:39:55,851
obstinate in her reply.

731
00:39:55,935 --> 00:39:57,561
"How could you say that?"

732
00:39:57,645 --> 00:40:00,606
"Of course they're real.
What are you talking about?"

733
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:04,860
But then she left immediately.

734
00:40:05,694 --> 00:40:07,696
[pensive music playing]

735
00:40:09,323 --> 00:40:15,579
Ian and I started to find pregnancy tests
in Ziploc bags with blue markers.

736
00:40:16,205 --> 00:40:17,832
I'm thinking, "Oh, my God."

737
00:40:17,915 --> 00:40:19,834
I thought, "Who is this person?"

738
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,879
Ian and I started to doubt
everything that Angela said

739
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:28,592
for that entire eight months
of being in Ian's life.

740
00:40:29,427 --> 00:40:31,929
{\an8}So we told the police everything.

741
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:36,016
[man] This is, to put it lightly,
a monster of a case.

742
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:39,019
And our job is to figure it out,

743
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,105
um, to find out who's doing what,

744
00:40:41,188 --> 00:40:43,899
and we appreciate you coming in here
and making a statement.

745
00:40:43,983 --> 00:40:46,777
-[Ian] No problem at all.
-[man] So let's talk about Angela.

746
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:50,364
You stated that your relationship
with Angela started January 2nd?

747
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:52,992
[Ian] We met at the Starbucks in Anaheim.

748
00:40:53,492 --> 00:40:56,203
We just hit it off.
She was just a sweetheart.

749
00:40:56,287 --> 00:40:59,707
Everything I ever wanted in a woman.

750
00:41:00,583 --> 00:41:01,500
Everything.

751
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:07,131
Ian brought everything
that we had found in the condo.

752
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:09,967
-[man] You have pregnancy tests.
-[Ian] I do.

753
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:14,513
This was found after she left.

754
00:41:14,597 --> 00:41:17,057
This is the one
that I was shown for the twins.

755
00:41:17,141 --> 00:41:18,225
It's obviously been peed on.

756
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:20,769
And then I found these two

757
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:23,814
with a different kind of line in it.

758
00:41:23,898 --> 00:41:27,109
-And then I found three different pens.
-[Leslie] All of these in the same box.

759
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:29,487
[Ian] And if you can tell
from the side here,

760
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,947
this one's been altered and opened up,
they all have.

761
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:34,492
-[man] So she drew the line in it.
-[Ian] She drew the line.

762
00:41:35,367 --> 00:41:39,079
[Leslie] Ian explained to the police
the sonogram was fake.

763
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:41,123
[Ian] This just about
killed me, all right.

764
00:41:41,207 --> 00:41:44,793
If you google "fake sonograms,"

765
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:48,672
that one comes up
at, like, number ten on Google Images.

766
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:50,841
With other people's names on it.

767
00:41:50,925 --> 00:41:52,927
[music turns ominous]

768
00:41:54,428 --> 00:41:59,892
Ian was disturbed by the whole thing
and sort of at a loss for what to do next.

769
00:41:59,975 --> 00:42:01,894
He was not in a great place.

770
00:42:01,977 --> 00:42:05,147
-[telephone line ringing]
-And he was calling Angela.

771
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:08,275
[Ian] <i>Hey. I knew you</i>
<i>weren't gonna answer, and that's fine.</i>

772
00:42:08,359 --> 00:42:10,110
<i>I just wanted to leave a message.</i>

773
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:14,406
<i>You lied about something</i>
<i>very, very severe.</i>

774
00:42:14,490 --> 00:42:17,701
<i>And I think you can understand that.</i>
<i>I think anybody else would too.</i>

775
00:42:18,494 --> 00:42:21,247
<i>I just hope</i>
<i>you're taking care of yourself. Bye.</i>

776
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:23,499
[telephone line ringing]

777
00:42:23,582 --> 00:42:24,917
<i>It's Ian.</i>

778
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,921
<i>Just trying to give you a call</i>
<i>to see if you were available to talk.</i>

779
00:42:29,004 --> 00:42:31,090
<i>The fact that I even</i>
<i>want to talk to you at this point</i>

780
00:42:31,173 --> 00:42:32,800
<i>probably means I really do love you.</i>

781
00:42:32,883 --> 00:42:35,219
<i>So… give me a call.</i>

782
00:42:35,302 --> 00:42:36,220
<i>Love you.</i>

783
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:41,767
After Angela left, I was starting
to uncover all sorts of wacky stuff.

784
00:42:41,850 --> 00:42:43,435
-[man] She lied about her job?
-[Ian] Yes.

785
00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:46,272
She admitted
that she did not have the job.

786
00:42:46,897 --> 00:42:49,608
It felt like an immense responsibility

787
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:54,405
to be sure that the police knew
that there was some doubt

788
00:42:55,030 --> 00:42:58,784
now applied to Angela's filings with them

789
00:42:58,867 --> 00:43:02,162
about Michelle's threats
of violence and rape.

790
00:43:02,246 --> 00:43:05,291
Because what's really happening?

791
00:43:05,374 --> 00:43:08,377
[dramatic music playing]

792
00:43:10,212 --> 00:43:11,338
Holy shit.

793
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:15,092
Did any of these emails

794
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:17,428
actually come from Michelle?

795
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:28,814
Is it possible
that Angela sent all of these emails

796
00:43:29,315 --> 00:43:31,317
to herself?

797
00:43:35,487 --> 00:43:38,574
Holy… fuck.

798
00:43:40,784 --> 00:43:42,578
What really happened in the garage?

799
00:43:43,912 --> 00:43:45,581
Was she attacked in the garage?

800
00:43:47,875 --> 00:43:49,918
Here is Michelle in jail.

801
00:43:50,461 --> 00:43:54,256
And who the hell knows
if that's the right person in jail?

802
00:43:56,592 --> 00:43:58,761
Is Angela the victim

803
00:43:58,844 --> 00:44:00,262
or the perpetrator?

804
00:44:03,307 --> 00:44:05,517
[pensive music playing]

805
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,394
[Ian] Have you talked to Angela at all?

806
00:44:08,187 --> 00:44:09,021
[man] No.

807
00:44:09,104 --> 00:44:10,147
[Ian] Have you tried?

808
00:44:10,230 --> 00:44:11,065
[man] No.

809
00:44:11,148 --> 00:44:12,900
[Leslie] We told the police,

810
00:44:12,983 --> 00:44:14,526
"Please look into this."

811
00:44:15,069 --> 00:44:18,113
"Figure out what's missing.
Go talk to Angela."

812
00:44:18,197 --> 00:44:21,367
-[telephone line ringing]
-[children chattering]

813
00:44:21,450 --> 00:44:23,327
[Cunha] <i>Hey, it's Detective Cunha.</i>

814
00:44:23,410 --> 00:44:24,411
[Angela] <i>Yeah.</i>

815
00:44:24,912 --> 00:44:26,664
[Cunha] <i>Just a couple of questions.</i>

816
00:44:27,414 --> 00:44:30,000
<i>Do you know Jason Rayburn at all?</i>

817
00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:31,585
[tense, pensive music playing]

818
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,796
[Angela] <i>It's a person I dated</i>
<i>a while ago.</i>

819
00:44:33,879 --> 00:44:35,130
[Cunha] <i>Okay.</i>

820
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:36,632
[Angela] <i>Obviously, much before Ian.</i>

821
00:44:36,715 --> 00:44:38,300
[Cunha] <i>Okay. And then,</i>

822
00:44:38,384 --> 00:44:40,636
<i>did you ever get sick?</i>

823
00:44:40,719 --> 00:44:45,933
<i>Did you ever get sick to the point</i>
<i>where there's talk about you had cancer?</i>

824
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:48,352
[Angela] <i>There was talk about it.</i>

825
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:51,146
<i>I went to have</i>
<i>skin cancer biopsies removed,</i>

826
00:44:51,230 --> 00:44:52,439
<i>and I was super stressed out.</i>

827
00:44:53,190 --> 00:44:55,317
[Cunha] <i>Okay, so no chemotherapy</i>
<i>or anything like that?</i>

828
00:44:55,401 --> 00:44:57,111
[Angela] <i>No, absolutely not.</i>

829
00:44:58,445 --> 00:44:59,905
A mindfuck?

830
00:44:59,988 --> 00:45:01,323
[unsettling music playing]

831
00:45:01,407 --> 00:45:05,202
Sorry, but I don't know
if anything that I know about her is true.

832
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:07,371
[pensive music playing]

833
00:45:07,454 --> 00:45:09,164
[Ian] I can't believe this is happening.

834
00:45:09,248 --> 00:45:10,124
[sighs]

835
00:45:10,207 --> 00:45:12,000
I feel like a fucking idiot.

836
00:45:12,501 --> 00:45:14,545
[Cunha] Who do you think's responsible?

837
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:17,756
I think Angela did it all.

838
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:19,216
[music turns ominous]

839
00:45:19,967 --> 00:45:21,677
When I look at these crazy emails,

840
00:45:23,178 --> 00:45:25,681
and the religious stuff and whatever,
the Lilith stuff,

841
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:27,808
and the Craigslist and the rapist,

842
00:45:28,308 --> 00:45:29,852
that could have been Angela.

843
00:45:30,436 --> 00:45:33,105
I leave the house, bam.
All of a sudden, she's attacked.

844
00:45:33,188 --> 00:45:34,606
I tried to move. He grabbed me.

845
00:45:34,690 --> 00:45:36,692
He had me pinned back
by the hair at the neck.

846
00:45:37,359 --> 00:45:38,527
[Ian] She's behind all this.

847
00:45:39,445 --> 00:45:43,282
It seems like I've been sleeping
with the enemy the entire time.

848
00:45:45,242 --> 00:45:47,035
Team 12's Kevin Kennedy joins us

849
00:45:47,119 --> 00:45:49,496
from the Live Alert Center
with a plot twist.

850
00:45:49,580 --> 00:45:50,414
Kev?

851
00:45:50,497 --> 00:45:51,874
[lively news theme playing]

852
00:45:51,957 --> 00:45:55,502
Michelle Hadley spent four months in jail
for a crime she didn't commit.

853
00:45:55,586 --> 00:45:58,338
Police say she was framed
by a vindictive woman

854
00:45:58,422 --> 00:46:02,259
who was willing to take
extraordinary actions to ruin her life.

855
00:46:02,342 --> 00:46:04,386
I started to question

856
00:46:05,095 --> 00:46:07,514
what her motive was.

857
00:46:08,849 --> 00:46:09,933
At some point,

858
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:15,397
I just remember Angela asking me
about Ian's relationship with Michelle.

859
00:46:15,898 --> 00:46:19,818
She seemed pretty curious
about how that ended.

860
00:46:19,902 --> 00:46:21,069
[ominous music playing]

861
00:46:21,153 --> 00:46:23,781
At one point, Angela looks over at me,
and she's crying.

862
00:46:23,864 --> 00:46:26,158
And she said, "I just feel like

863
00:46:26,742 --> 00:46:28,827
Michelle is always gonna be in our life."

864
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:34,166
"We're never going to be able to move on
because she will always be a part of it."

865
00:46:34,750 --> 00:46:37,294
[woman on TV] <i>The judge</i>
<i>used the words "evil, calculated,"</i>

866
00:46:37,377 --> 00:46:39,046
<i>and said what Angela Diaz did</i>

867
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:42,466
<i>was unlike anything he had seen</i>
<i>in all his years on the bench.</i>

868
00:46:42,549 --> 00:46:46,887
This was a distorted triangle
of relationships

869
00:46:46,970 --> 00:46:50,390
that twisted fantasies
aren't even made up of.

870
00:46:51,725 --> 00:46:54,728
[somber music playing]

871
00:47:13,121 --> 00:47:15,624
[Michelle] They told me I'm free to go

872
00:47:15,707 --> 00:47:17,960
and the charges
have been completely dropped.

873
00:47:18,043 --> 00:47:21,046
-[auspicious music playing]
-[camera shutters clicking]

874
00:47:22,756 --> 00:47:27,219
Freedom was so sweet at that point
because, oh man, I mean,

875
00:47:27,302 --> 00:47:30,013
you don't appreciate it
until you've lost it.

876
00:47:31,473 --> 00:47:34,059
I'm walking down the courthouse steps,

877
00:47:34,142 --> 00:47:37,020
and the media is waiting for me outside.

878
00:47:40,023 --> 00:47:42,609
It's this big moment for me

879
00:47:42,693 --> 00:47:47,656
because they all want to hear
what I have to say.

880
00:47:47,739 --> 00:47:51,410
Obviously, this has been
a huge nightmare for me,

881
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:55,622
probably the most traumatic
experience of my life.

882
00:47:55,706 --> 00:48:00,836
And I'm glad it's finally over,
and I finally get to move on with my life.

883
00:48:00,919 --> 00:48:03,422
Here's a bizarre
Orange County love triangle.

884
00:48:03,505 --> 00:48:04,673
This is a big story.

885
00:48:04,756 --> 00:48:07,551
[man on TV]
It had all the makings of <i>Law and Order.</i>

886
00:48:07,634 --> 00:48:10,679
A jealous wife,
romantic rivals, blackmail.

887
00:48:11,263 --> 00:48:16,268
I think the media
gleefully grabbed ahold of this narrative

888
00:48:16,351 --> 00:48:20,105
of the crazy woman,

889
00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:22,816
the jealous woman.

890
00:48:24,318 --> 00:48:27,487
And if they couldn't paint me as that,

891
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:29,948
then they were
just gonna paint Angela as that.

892
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:34,202
They didn't want to talk about the man.
Nobody wanted to talk about that.

893
00:48:34,286 --> 00:48:36,121
I wanted someone to listen to me.

894
00:48:37,414 --> 00:48:40,542
I wanted to tell someone
what actually happened.

895
00:48:41,209 --> 00:48:43,670
Because there was a lot more to tell.

896
00:48:43,754 --> 00:48:46,757
[music turns dramatic]

897
00:48:53,221 --> 00:48:55,891
[man] I was working
at the Department of Justice

898
00:48:55,974 --> 00:48:59,144
as a criminal investigator
and digital forensic examiner,

899
00:48:59,227 --> 00:49:03,106
investigating cases involving
Department of Justice employees.

900
00:49:04,107 --> 00:49:06,276
My name is Ian. I'm a U.S. Marshal.

901
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:08,195
Sorry, this is Angela.

902
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:10,530
[man] Angela Connell had pleaded guilty

903
00:49:10,614 --> 00:49:15,118
to charges relating to framing
Ian Diaz's ex-girlfriend, Michelle Hadley.

904
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:18,080
{\an8}Ian Diaz was
a Deputy United States Marshal

905
00:49:18,163 --> 00:49:20,332
{\an8}and a Department of Justice employee.

906
00:49:20,415 --> 00:49:24,711
I mean, we had an obligation
to go back to look at the case again.

907
00:49:24,795 --> 00:49:27,547
So we reached out
to Anaheim Police Department…

908
00:49:27,631 --> 00:49:29,967
[tense, pensive music playing]

909
00:49:30,592 --> 00:49:33,971
…and they provided us
with their case file.

910
00:49:34,763 --> 00:49:39,267
{\an8}One of the first things I did
was listen to the interview with Ian Diaz.

911
00:49:39,768 --> 00:49:41,019
[music stops]

912
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:44,189
[man] <i>This is, to put it lightly,</i>
<i>a monster of a case.</i>

913
00:49:44,272 --> 00:49:46,525
<i>Our job is to find out who's doing what,</i>

914
00:49:46,608 --> 00:49:48,944
<i>and that's why</i>
<i>we pulled you in here to talk to you.</i>

915
00:49:49,027 --> 00:49:51,363
<i>We appreciate you coming in</i>
<i>and making a statement.</i>

916
00:49:51,446 --> 00:49:54,282
[Ian] <i>Right, tell me some good news</i>
<i>because my heart is up.</i>

917
00:49:54,366 --> 00:49:55,784
-[man] <i>Okay.</i>
-[Ian] <i>What is going on?</i>

918
00:49:56,576 --> 00:49:59,746
[Jason] My general impression
of Ian and his responses

919
00:49:59,830 --> 00:50:02,207
is that he's a bit anxious.

920
00:50:02,290 --> 00:50:04,626
[pensive music playing]

921
00:50:04,710 --> 00:50:07,087
{\an8}In addition to those recordings,

922
00:50:07,170 --> 00:50:10,424
{\an8}there were a few things
in the body camera footage

923
00:50:10,507 --> 00:50:11,758
{\an8}that jumped out to me.

924
00:50:12,467 --> 00:50:14,302
There is a scene

925
00:50:14,886 --> 00:50:17,264
where Ian leaves the living room

926
00:50:17,347 --> 00:50:20,142
while Angela is talking to the police.

927
00:50:20,225 --> 00:50:22,227
[officer 1] <i>The specifics of that.</i>

928
00:50:22,310 --> 00:50:24,604
<i>-Like, exactly when it…?</i>
-[officer 1] <i>Time? Date?</i>

929
00:50:24,688 --> 00:50:27,691
<i>Oh, no, she doesn't say,</i>
<i>like, on December 16th.</i>

930
00:50:27,774 --> 00:50:30,318
Ian is clearly listening
to what Angela is saying

931
00:50:30,902 --> 00:50:34,698
and provides her information
from the side.

932
00:50:34,781 --> 00:50:36,241
<i>No, she doesn't do that.</i>

933
00:50:36,324 --> 00:50:38,326
[Ian] <i>She says, "I'm coming over tonight."</i>

934
00:50:38,410 --> 00:50:39,494
<i>She always says that.</i>

935
00:50:39,578 --> 00:50:41,455
<i>She always says that threat of, like,</i>

936
00:50:41,538 --> 00:50:43,498
<i>"I'm coming over tonight.</i>
<i>I'm coming over."</i>

937
00:50:43,999 --> 00:50:47,377
It sounds to me
as if Ian is trying to coach Angela.

938
00:50:49,212 --> 00:50:51,256
